        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Verant or the people at VI / SOE clearly hate the necro class. I have sat back (well in truth I have raised a ruckus over every point to no avail) and watched this happen. Now I feel it is time for an accounting.

If you have any other clear necro class nerfs then please post them here. Perhaps we might get some action when VI realizes that our class has been utterly worked over and left for dead.

1. Necro spell resists. Our spells are much more resistable than any other classes at any level.

2. Necro group buffs. We were given a set of group buffs. Sadly they clash so badly with so many things they are often worthless. Does anyone have any kind of explanation why Zefeers Theft of Vitae would not stick if a player has Grim Aura? Why do our reverse hitpoint heals not stick if the recipient is dotted? Why does our Degeneration spell dramtically lower agility? etc. etc. etc.

3. Necro mana regen. Strange that we are the only class that cannot benefit from enchanter based mana regen buffs.

4. Necro versus Enchanter Dire Charm. We can only DC undead, Ench can DC anything. Ench can DC mobs two levels higher than we can - considering that they have no restriction at all on the class of mob they DC (undead, summoned, plant, animal, npc) surely they should be restricted to mobs two levels lower than Necros and Druids?

5. Necro Lifeburn versus Wizard Manaburn. Why does necro lifeburn not stack yet Manaburn does?

6. Cosmetically. Why was our gradually upgradded badass looking pet series taken away from us and replaced with a single model that looks like it is walking with a cold iron rod shoved up it's rear end?

7. In what way does our epic look like a Scythe? Oh no it looks like a quacking duck - very very dangerous looking - my ass. There are inumerable weapons that look vastly more intimidating than our "quack stick".

8. Why is the necro epic so insanely hard to get? Forget the fact that it "can be bought" - the components are insanely rare drops.

9. Why is our level 59 pet, with no exceptions on any server, the rarest level 59 spell in the game. Substantially more rare than most level 60 spells?

10. Why is the necro focus book so incredibly rare? Over 30 trips to Hate, seen the broodmaster only 4 times and he has not dropped the book once.

11. Why are we prevented from casting our spells multiple times? Yes I do mean stacking our own dots. Last I checked our mana pool was no bigger than anyone of equal level / int / manaitems. Last I checked a Wizard can chain nuke with their biggest nukes doing nearly as much damage as our biggest dots and they don't have a "stacking" issue.

12. Why are there ZERO focus items cast by wizards that will improve DOT's? There are focus items for every other kind of spell.

13. Why do we get our last non-lifetap DD at level 55, which happens to be equivalent damage wise to our level 44 DD?

14. Why is that level 55 DD (Conglaciation of Bone) only dropped off one **LEVEL 70** mob in the entire game? Anyone know any other 55damage DD that is dropped off a level 70 mob?

15. Why is Dead Men Floating, only dropped ***RARELY*** off a single mob in the entire game? It is a group beneficial buff, it does nothing for us individually.......??????

16. Why is our resistance debuff spell line so resistable that it is not even worth scribing into our spellboook let alone trying to cast?

Why do Verant never ever, I mean not once in the entire time I have played this game, checked to see what effect their latest patch is going to have on the necromancer class? Without fail it screws us over in some way.

This latest patch, supposedly aimed at fixing the ongoing problems dot stacking problems has been the absolute worst ever for our class. Sure they are possibly going to fix some of the horrendous problems they have created. But the point has to be that they NEVER BOTHERED TO TEST ANY OF THESE CHANGES ON THE CLASS THAT THEY WERE SUPPOSED TO AID.

I have absolutely no doubt in my mind that ***SOMEONE*** at VI has a serious mental block with the necro class and is trying hard to damage it gradually until no-one wants to play the class any more. All I can say to this dim-witted person or persons is:-

This is a roleplaying game - get over your petty inability to accept that and get rid of your obvious bias against the Necromancer class.



Edited by - Infernall on 10/10/2002  12:04:22
[/quote]</textarea><br>
        </td>
      </tr>

