 nukes doing nearly as much damage as our biggest dots and they don't have a "stacking" issue."</P><P>All wizards have is damage, we have much much more.  If we could stack dots we'd be forced to use all of our mana for dots, I'd rather be more useful, shrug...solo dot stacking isn't something you'll see verant implementing anytime soon.</P><P>"12. Why are there ZERO focus items cast by wizards that will improve DOT's? There are focus items for every other kind of spell."</P><P>Magicians I believe you mean, I'm not sure about this one either though.  We do however get very nice ones.  I just got one that increases my dots by 20%.</P><P>"13. Why do we get our last non-lifetap DD at level 55, which happens to be equivalent damage wise to our level 44 DD?"</P><P>Ancient: Lifebane.  Check it out.</P><P>"14. Why is that level 55 DD (Conglaciation of Bone) only dropped off one **LEVEL 70** mob in the entire game? Anyone know any other 55damage DD that is dropped off a level 70 mob?"</P><P>Why complain? The spell sucks anyway, heh.  Would you complain if I had a bottle of spoiled milk 50 feet above your head and you had nothing to get it with?  Probably not.</P><P>"15. Why is Dead Men Floating, only dropped ***RARELY*** off a single mob in the entire game? It is a group beneficial buff, it does nothing for us individually.......??????"</P><P>This is like a warrior complaining that primal doesn't drop off orc pawns, his DPS would increase and that benefits the group he's in!  Guess what, some things are just the way they are, you have to deal because they won't be changed.  This spell was implemented on the chardok revamp I believe, they wanted chardok to be more beneficial to group in.  Didn't really work though.</P><P>"16. Why is our resistance debuff spell line so resistable that it is not even worth scribing into our spellboook let alone trying to cast?"</P><P>Again, I've had no problem sticking this on mobs that aren't immune to the spell.  The point of this spell is to lower the resists, obviously the spell will resist if the resists aren't low.</P><P>Your gripes are so lowly that it would be a waste of time for verant to fix 90% of them, there are things that NEED to be fixed, none of those things are here.  Sorry bud, but I don't agree with most of your post.</P><P>Necromancer is a great class in its current state, open your eyes to your surroundings.  Of course there are better classes than us, who cares.</P><P>Edited by - Moonspark on 09/21/2002  03:42:28</font></td>
